{
  "texts": [
    "4) Self-supervised learning and weakly supervised learning.",
    "Self-supervised learning [190] and weakly supervised learning [191] are important directions for the future development of large AI models.",
    "Self-supervised learning allows models to learn the inherent structure and patterns in the data by designing appropriate self-supervised tasks.",
    "Weakly supervised learning guides the model learning through weaker supervision signals, such as partial annotations and domain knowledge.",
    "Such methods can better utilize existing data resources, reduce annotation costs, and achieve better results wen data are scarce."
  ]
}